cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

The paper deals with deep learning and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations of convolutional networks and proposes a new solution, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions reinforcement learning and robotics, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.RO (Robotics) as possible sub-categories.
